article.headline: Northeastern 62, Hofstra 53
article.story: EDS: Northeastern 62, Hofstra 53. HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Matt Janning scored 19 points to lead Northeastern to a 62-53 victory over Hofstra on Wednesday night. Chasson Allen and Eugene Spates each added 11 points for the Huskies (12-12, 8-6 Colonial Athletic Association), while Manny Adako added 10. Freshman Charles Jenkins had 14 points for the Pride (8-16, 5-9), while Antoine Agudio, the nation's 12th-leading scorer with a 22.7 average, was held to 13 and Darren Townes added 12. Janning had eight points as the Huskies opened a 19-10 lead. Hofstra closed within 23-22 but the Huskies went 10-4 the rest of the half for a seven-point halftime lead. Adako's jumper with 14:05 left gave Northeastern its largest lead, 44-34. Hofstra went on an 11-2 run to get within 46-45 on a jumper by Greg Johnson with 9:05 left. Jenkins' layup got the Pride within 55-51 with 1:05 left but the Huskies made seven free throws the rest of the way, four by Allen.
